quran[59]{c,v,t}:
  26,52,"And We communicated to Musa that, \"Take away my servants by night, you will be pursued"
  26,53,So Firawn sent into the cities (his officials) who gathered (people)
  26,54,"(saying), \"They are certainly a small party"
  26,55,and they have angered us
  26,56,and we are an alert army
  26,57,Thus did We drive them out from gardens and springs
  26,58,and treasures and an honoured position
  26,59,Like that (it happened). And We made the children of Israel to inherit them
  26,60,So they pursued them at sunrise
  26,61,"So when the two parties saw each other, the companions of Musa said, \"We are caught"
  26,62,"He said, \"By no means, My Fosterer is certainly with me, He will guide me"
  26,63,"So We communicated to Musa that, \"Strike the sea with your staff,\" so it was split and each part became like a great mountain"
  26,64,"And We brought others near, there (at the same place)"
  26,65,"and We delivered Musa and those with him, all together"
  26,66,then We drowned the others
  26,67,"In that there is certainly a sign, but the majority of them does not believe"
  26,68,"And your Fosterer, He is certainly the Mighty, the Merciful"
  26,69,And Tell them the story of Abraham
  26,70,"when he said to his father and his people, \"What do you worship"
  26,71,"They said, \"We worship idols and we will remain sticking to them"
  26,72,"He said, \"Do they listen to you when you pray to (them)"
  26,73,or benefit you or harm you
  26,74,"They said, \"No, we found our fathers doing like that"
  26,75,"He said, \"Then do you see, that which you worship"
  26,76,you and your fathers before you
  26,77,For they are enemies to me except the Fosterer of the worlds
  26,78,"Who created me, then He it is Who guides me"
  26,79,and Who feeds me and gives me to drink
  26,80,"and when I am sick, then He it is Who cures me"
  26,81,"and Who will cause me to die, then give me life (again)"
  26,82,"and (from) Whom I hope, that He will protectively forgive me my mistakes on the day of judgment"
  26,83,My Fosterer! grant me wisdom and join me with the righteous
  26,84,and assign for me a true mention among later (generations)
  26,85,and place me among the inheritors of the garden of bliss
  26,86,"and protectively forgive my father, he is certainly among those who are astray"
  26,87,and do not disgrace me on the day they are raised (again)
  26,88,the day on which neither wealth nor sons will benefit
  26,89,except him who comes to Allah with a pure heart
  26,90,And the garden will be brought near for those who guard (against evil)
  26,91,And the hell will be made manifest to the erring ones
  26,92,"And it will be said to them, \"Where are those whom you used to worship"
  26,93,besides Allah? Can they help you or help themselves
  26,94,"Then they will be thrown headlong into it, they and the misleaders"
  26,95,"and the army of Iblis (devil), all together"
  26,96,They will say while they quarrel therein
  26,97,"By Allah, we were certainly in clear error"
  26,98,when we considered you equal to the Fosterer of the worlds
  26,99,and no one has misled us except the criminals
  26,100,so we have no mediators
  26,101,and no intimate friend
  26,102,"So if we are given (another chance to) return (to the world), then we will certainly be of those who believe"
  26,103,"There is certainly a sign in that, but the majority of them does not believe"
  26,104,"And your Fosterer, He is certainly the Mighty, the Merciful"
  26,105,The people of Nuh denied the messengers
  26,106,"when their brother Nuh said to them, \"Will you not guard (against evil)"
  26,107,I am certainly a trustworthy messenger to you
  26,108,so fear Allah and obey me
  26,109,"and l do not ask you for any reward for it, my reward is with none but the Fosterer of the worlds"
  26,110,so fear Allah and obey me